You are a senior interviewer and subject-matter expert.

I am preparing for an interview for the role of <ROLE> with <EXPERIENCE_LEVEL> experience.

Topic to prepare: <TOPIC>

Teach me this topic in a structured, interview-oriented way.

Your response must include:

1. Conceptual Foundation
   - Explain the topic from first principles
   - Why it exists and what problems it solves
   - Where it fits in real-world systems/architecture

2. Core Components & Terminology
   - Key concepts, components, and terminology
   - Diagrams explained in words (no images needed)
   - Common configurations or patterns

3. Hands-On / Practical Understanding
   - How it works step-by-step in real production environments
   - Commands, configuration examples, or pseudo-code (where applicable)
   - Common defaults vs recommended best practices

4. Interview-Focused Q&A
   - Beginner-level questions with concise answers
   - Intermediate-level questions with explanations
   - Advanced/scenario-based questions with reasoning
   - "Why" and "How" questions interviewers actually ask

5. Common Mistakes & Misconceptions
   - Typical errors candidates make
   - Incorrect assumptions to avoid
   - Traps interviewers set

6. Comparison Section (if applicable)
   - Compare this topic with related technologies or alternatives
   - When to use what, and why

7. Real-World Use Cases
   - Enterprise or production use cases
   - Scaling, security, failure handling considerations
   - Monitoring and troubleshooting overview

8. One-Page Interview Revision Sheet
   - Key bullets to revise before the interview
   - Important commands / keywords
   - 30-second, 2-minute, and 5-minute explanation versions

9. Mock Interview
   - Ask me 5 interview questions one by one
   - Wait for my answer
   - Review my answer and suggest improvements

Tone:
- Clear, structured, and interview-ready
- Assume I know basics but want strong clarity and confidence
- Avoid unnecessary theory; focus on what matters in interviews
